meta.name: NMR chemical shieldings
meta.description:
This map was generated using KPCovR with α=0.5
and 2 principal components, using NMR chemical shielding as biaising property
and SOAP structural descriptors.

The structures and properties come from a database of energy and NMR chemical
shifts DFT calculations of various molecular materials taken from the Cambridge
Structural Database containing only H/C/N/O/S atoms, with atoms randomly rattled
around their equilibrium structures.
references: *Structure-Property Maps with Kernel Principal Covariates Regression* B. A. Helfrecht, R. K. Cersonsky, G. Fraux, M. Ceriotti, https://arxiv.org/abs/2002.05076

*Chemical Shifts in Molecular Solids by Machine Learning Datasets*, M. Ceriotti, L. Emsley, F. Paruzzo, A. Hofstetter, F. Musil, S. De, E. A. Engel, and A. Anelli, Materials Cloud Archive 2019.0023/v2 (2019), https://doi.org/10.24435/materialscloud:2019.0023/v2
